    <stitle>No Idle APU/HVAC System - MAINTENANCE - Replacing Air Filter</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Replacing Air Filter</title>
        <figure id="f1603721" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603721.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                     scalefitheight="352px"/>
            <caption>Figure 21. Replacing Air Filter</caption>
        </figure>
        <seqlist style="arabic">
            <item>
                <para>Replace engine air filter as per routine maintenance schedule or as necessary.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Release the two retaining clips on the side of the air cleaner housing cap.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Remove the old air filter element by pulling it straight out of housing.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Insert the new air filter.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Re-install air cleaner housing cap ensuring evacuator valve is pointing to the ground.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Be careful not to knock dust from the dirty filter.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Evacuator valve must point to the ground.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
